reason - Variable in class com.ringcentral.definitions.CallLogRecordLegInfo
Reason of a call result: * `Accepted` - The call was connected to and accepted by this number * `Connected` - The call was answered, but there was no response on how to handle the call (for example, a voice mail system answered the call and did not push "1" to accept) * `Line Busy` - The phone number you dialed was busy * `Not Answered` - The phone number you dialed was not answered * `No Answer` - You did not answer the call * `Hang Up` - The caller hung up before the call was answered * `Stopped` - This attempt was stopped because the call was answered by another phone * `Internal Error` - An internal error occurred when making the call.
